<%- include('../partials/header') %>

  <style>
    .blog-post-page {
      background: #676964;
      min-height: 100vh;
      padding-top: 100px;
    }

    .blog-card {
      background: #c5c5c3;
      border-radius: 2rem;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);
      border: 0;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .blog-header-img {
      height: 400px;
      background-size: cover;
      background-position: center;
      border-radius: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }

    .highlight-box {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.05) 0%, rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.05) 100%);
      border-left: 5px solid #6366f1;
      border-radius: 1rem;
      padding: 2rem;
      margin: 2.5rem 0;
    }

    .step-roadmap {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 3rem;
    }

    .step-roadmap::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      left: 15px;
      top: 0;
      bottom: 0;
      width: 2px;
      background: rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.1);
    }

    .step-item {
      position: relative;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    .step-number {
      position: absolute;
      left: -48px;
      width: 32px;
      height: 32px;
      background: #6366f1;
      color: rgb(19, 17, 17);
      border-radius: 50%;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(99, 102, 241, 0.3);
    }

    .yt-search-box {
      background: #1e1b4b;
      border-radius: 1.5rem;
      padding: 2.5rem;
      color: rgb(180, 196, 90);
      text-align: center;
      margin: 3rem 0;
    }

    .btn-yt {
      background: #ef4444;
      color: rgb(19, 17, 17);
      border: none;
      padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-weight: 700;
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }

    .btn-yt:hover {
      background: #dc2626;
      transform: scale(1.05);
      color: rgb(12, 11, 11);
    }

    .blog-content p {
      color: #4b5563;
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    .blog-content h2 {
      color: #111827;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-top: 3.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    /* ── Reading Progress Bar ── */
    .progress-container {
      position: fixed;
      top: 0;
      left: 0;
      width: 100%;
      height: 5px;
      z-index: 9999;
      background: transparent;
    }

    .progress-bar-top {
      height: 5px;
      background: linear-gradient(to right, #6366f1, #ec4899);
      width: 0%;
    }

    /* ── Checklist Items ── */
    .checklist-item {
      background: #535c91;
      border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
      border-radius: 1rem;
      padding: 1.25rem;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      transition: all 0.2s ease;
    }

    .checklist-item:hover {
      border-color: #6366f1;
      background: rgba(204, 202, 91, 0.02);
      transform: translateX(5px);
    }

    .checklist-icon {
      width: 24px;
      height: 24px;
      color: #6366f1;
      margin-right: 1rem;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      margin-top: 3px;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="progress-container">
    <div class="progress-bar-top" id="topProgress"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="blog-post-page pb-5">
    <div class="container py-5">
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-10 col-xl-9">

          <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
          <nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="mb-5">
            <ol class="breadcrumb">
              <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/" class="text-secondary text-decoration-none small">Home</a></li>
              <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a href="/blog" class="text-secondary text-decoration-none small">Blog</a>
              </li>
              <li class="breadcrumb-item active small" aria-current="page">No Motivation?</li>
            </ol>
          </nav>

          <article class="blog-card p-4 p-md-5">
            <!-- Article Header -->
            <header class="mb-5 text-center">
              <span class="badge bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-3 py-2 rounded-pill mb-4 fw-bold"
                style="background:#a9b86a; color: #4338ca;">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-brain me-2"></i>Mindset Masterclass
              </span>
              <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold mb-4" style="letter-spacing: -1px;">No Motivation? Start 2 AM Study With Me
              </h1>
              <p class="lead text-muted mx-auto" style="max-width: 700px;">
                Your desk feels like a desert, your books feel like lead. Here is the exact psychological roadmap to
                break the stalemate tonight.
              </p>
            </header>

            <div class="blog-header-img shadow-sm"
              style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1517842645767-c639042777db?q=80&w=2070&auto=format&fit=crop');">
            </div>

            <div class="blog-content fs-5">
              <p>
                It’s 11:00 PM. You have an exam in three days, a stack of notes that looks like a mountain,
                and exactly <strong>zero motivation</strong> to start. You’ve scrolled through every social media app
                twice,
                and now you’re just staring at your lamp, feeling that heavy weight of guilt in your chest.
              </p>

              <h2 id="motivation-trap"><i class="fa-solid fa-thumbtack text-primary me-3"></i>The Motivation Trap</h2>
              <p>
                The biggest mistake students make is waiting for "motivation" to arrive.
                Think of motivation like a fair-weather friend; it shows up when things are easy
                and disappears when the work gets tough.
              </p>
              <p>
                The secret? <strong>Action creates motivation.</strong> Not the other way around.
                Once you start—even for just 5 minutes—your brain shifts from "procrastination mode" (fear)
                to "task mode" (execution). It's physics: an object in motion stays in motion.
              </p>

              <div class="highlight-box">
                <h4 class="fw-bold mb-3 d-flex align-items-center">
                  <i class="fa-solid fa-flask-vial text-indigo-600 me-3"></i> The Science of "Body Doubling"
                </h4>
                <p class="mb-0 text-dark">
                  Studying in a library is 10x more effective than studying in your bedroom.
                  When your brain sees others working, it releases subtle signals that "this is the time to focus."
                  By studying "with us" using a digital hub, you trick your brain into Focus Mode.
                </p>
              </div>

              <h2 id="quick-start"><i class="fa-solid fa-map-location-dot text-primary me-3"></i>The Quick-Start Roadmap
              </h2>
              <div class="step-roadmap mt-5">
                <div class="step-item">
                  <div class="step-number">1</div>
                  <h5 class="fw-bold">Clear the Visual Chaos</h5>
                  <p class="text-muted small mb-0">Don't clean the whole room. Just clear exactly 1 square foot of desk
                    space. Your brain needs an "oasis of calm" to start.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="step-item">
                  <div class="step-number">2</div>
                  <h5 class="fw-bold">Set Your Micro-Goal</h5>
                  <p class="text-muted small mb-0">Open the <a href="/clock" class="text-indigo-600 fw-bold">Clock
                      Hub</a> and type in "Read 2 Pages." Not the whole chapter—just 2 pages.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="step-item">
                  <div class="step-number">3</div>
                  <h5 class="fw-bold">The 25-Minute Contract</h5>
                  <p class="text-muted small mb-0">Start the <a href="/timer" class="text-indigo-600 fw-bold">Pomodoro
                      Timer</a>. You are legally allowed to stop after 25 minutes. (But you won't.)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="step-item">
                  <div class="step-number">4</div>
                  <h5 class="fw-bold">Mask the Silence</h5>
                  <p class="text-muted small mb-0">Choose a Lofi vibe from the <a href="/music"
                      class="text-indigo-600 fw-bold">Music Room</a>. Silence feeds overthinking; ambient beats feed
                    productivity.</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- YouTube CTA -->
              <div class="yt-search-box shadow-lg">
                <i class="fa-brands fa-youtube fa-4x text-danger mb-4"></i>
                <h3 class="fw-bold mb-3">Don't Overthink. Just Watch.</h3>
                <p class="mb-4 opacity-75">Sometimes you just need to see someone else doing it. Search for our "Study
                  With Me" sessions and let's work together.</p>
                <a href="https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=2+am+study+with+me+youtube+channel"
                  target="_blank" class="btn btn-yt">
                  <i class="fa-solid fa-magnifying-glass me-2"></i> Search "2 am study with me youtube channel"
                </a>
              </div>

              <h2 id="science"><i class="fa-solid fa-microscope text-primary me-3"></i>Why This Works</h2>
              <div class="row g-4 mb-5">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <div class="checklist-item h-100">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-user-group checklist-icon"></i>
                    <span><strong>Not Alone:</strong> Seeing others work reduces the feeling of isolation and
                      study-fatigue.</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <div class="checklist-item h-100">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved checklist-icon"></i>
                    <span><strong>Reduces Procrastination:</strong> The shared environment creates a "social contract"
                      to stay focused.</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <div class="checklist-item h-100">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-clock-rotate-left checklist-icon"></i>
                    <span><strong>Builds Discipline:</strong> Consistent study-with-me habits train your brain to enter
                      deep focus faster.</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <div class="checklist-item h-100">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-wand-magic-sparkles checklist-icon"></i>
                    <span><strong>Real Study Vibes:</strong> Creates an immersive environment even if you're in a noisy
                      dorm or bedroom.</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <h2 id="final-thoughts"><i class="fa-solid fa-check-double text-success me-3"></i>Final Thoughts</h2>
              <p>
                You don't need a 5-hour study block to be productive. You just need to win the fight against
                the <strong>first 300 seconds</strong>. Use the tools at 2 AM Study to build your own digital library
                and let the environment do the heavy lifting for you.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-5 text-center mb-5">
                <a href="/timer" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg rounded-pill px-5 fw-bold shadow-lg py-3">
                  Start My Timer Now <i class="fa-solid fa-bolt ms-2"></i>
                </a>
              </p>
            </div>

            <hr class="my-5 opacity-5">
            <footer class="d-flex align-items-center bg-light p-4 rounded-4 border-0">
              <div class="flex-shrink-0">
                <div
                  class="rounded-circle bg-indigo-600 text-white d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center shadow"
                  style="width: 64px; height: 64px;">
                  <i class="fa-solid fa-feather-pointed fa-lg"></i>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="ms-4">
                <h6 class="fw-bold mb-1 text-dark">The 2AM Editorial Team</h6>
                <p class="text-muted small mb-0">Curating the best productivity hacks and mindset shifts for over 50,000
                  students worldwide.</p>
              </div>
            </footer>

            <div class="mt-5 d-flex flex-column flex-md-row justify-content-between align-items-center gap-3">
              <a href="/blog" class="btn btn-link text-decoration-none text-secondary fw-bold p-0">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-left-long me-2"></i> Back to Blog
              </a>
              <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-3">
                <span class="text-muted small fw-bold">SHARE THIS GUIDE:</span>
                <a href="#" class="text-secondary"><i class="fa-brands fa-x-twitter"></i></a>
                <a href="#" class="text-secondary"><i class="fa-brands fa-facebook-f"></i></a>
                <a href="#" class="text-secondary"><i class="fa-brands fa-linkedin-in"></i></a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    window.onscroll = function () {
      var winScroll = document.body.scrollTop || document.documentElement.scrollTop;
      var height = document.documentElement.scrollHeight - document.documentElement.clientHeight;
      var scrolled = (winScroll / height) * 100;
      document.getElementById("topProgress").style.width = scrolled + "%";
    };
  </script>
  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>